oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Mt. Olivet Interment Record Book, Volume II
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Volume II of interment books recording burials in Mount Olivet Cemetery from 1855-1891. Data recorded includes Name, Date of Interment, Cause of Death, and plot location.

Mount Olivet Cemetery is a 206-acre cemetery in Nashville, Tennessee. It was established in 1856 by Adrian Van Sinderen Lindsley and John Buddeke. Notable interments include John Overton, Thomas Ryman, Anne Dallas Dudley and multiple fomer governors of Tennessee.
